title: Grateful Dead Live at Giants Stadium on 1978-09-02
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Dire Wolf, Looks Like Rain, Stagger Lee, I Need A Miracle, Peggy-O, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication

Set 2

Good Lovin', Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

Other artist(s): NRPS & Willie Nelson

reviews.review_text:
highlights This show is a post hiatus highlight, given the best Fire of all time and the best Bobby Good Lovin'. The jam after the second verse of Eyes had Giants Stadium lifting off. 
This is another excellent dusborne matrix. Check out the Althea from 5/15/80.
- A good show, but certainly nothing special

Broken Bone Billy had a cast on his wrist/hand/forearm.  During the drums/ he played a conga with his elbow like a wildman igniting the crowd.  I was way up close (way) and it seems like nobody remembers this, yet I thought they had a big video screen showing the action as well.....???  After labor day weekend 77' at Raceway Park, Englishtown (Old Bridge) New Jersey, I saw a bunch of shows, but had high hopes for this one; but (it seemed) the audience had a lot of people checking out this newly talked about scene (that had been building since 76 - 77 - 78) without any special affinity for entheogens and ecstatic dancing.

Fantastic Matrix @Dave Usborne --

Just outstanding work on a very worthy show.  Man is this fun to listen to.

Thank You
